I'm not sure how anyone could give this game less than 5 stars. It's incredible.  It's simple to play, full of hidden surprises, and open to creativity!   For instance instruments can be found here and there, and the friends will play music together. Not every guy likes every instrument. The pig likes the trumpet but not the guitar. It seems squirrel is happy to play anything but he is really groovy. He has a pirate ship tree house with a disco ball after all.  I still want to try to get them in matching hats or bring their teddy bears together or see what happens if I get them all tools and worming together. It's hard for me to get time to play because it's my toddler's game.  This game is very suitable for 2 to 4 year olds, and models friendly interactions as well as independence. The friends are nice, but they don't all like the same things. That goes for food and activities as well as instruments. None like sleeping in the other one's bed. They all seem okay driving each other's cars. Pig doesn't like swimming but some of the others do.  This game is really so well done, of all toddler games this is my favorite - and we have tried most. I like this better than the sago mini and Dr panda games. There is so much to do and discover, and much of it isn't obvious. Also unlike other games, this one allows for independent play and creativity. Sadly the other pango games seem either less vast or too complex for a very young player.   Suggestions for pango:  Expansions? I'll pay! A car more than one guy can ride in? Ability to build up the tree house if this isn't already built in Instead of street signs to fast travel, a menu to jump to houses similar to the menu to bring friends  Ability to build a boat or something if this isn't already built in
